If the 2014 NBA draft goes as currently projected in June, eight of the top 10 picks in the draft will be teenagers who have played only one year of college basketball. The most coveted prospects in the draft -- Andrew Wiggins, Jabari Parker, Joel Embiid, Julius Randle, Aaron Gordon, Noah Vonleh and Tyler Ennis -- are all college freshmen. However, if new NBA commissioner Adam Silver gets his way, they might be the last freshman class to be able to declare for the draft. To read Chad Ford's full story on new age restrictions in the NBA, sign up for Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Chad FordSenior Writer, NBA Insider Follow Archive Senior NBA Writer for ESPN.com ESPN Insider NBA Draft Analyst since 2002 Writes ESPN's NBA Draft Top 100 and Lottery Mock Draft